# Dialog and Sheet Accessibility Rule

- Root cause: Radix `DialogContent`/`SheetContent` logs accessibility warnings when no title is rendered in the content tree.
- Project safeguard: shared UI wrappers inject hidden fallback titles, but feature code must still provide explicit titles.
- Every `DialogContent` must include a `DialogTitle` in its rendered tree.
- Every `SheetContent` must include a `SheetTitle` in its rendered tree.
- Prefer explicit structure: `DialogHeader` + `DialogTitle` (+ `DialogDescription` when useful).
- Prefer explicit structure: `SheetHeader` + `SheetTitle` (+ `SheetDescription` when useful).
- For `DialogContent`, provide either:
  - an explicit `DialogDescription`, or
  - `aria-describedby={undefined}` when description is intentionally omitted.
- For `SheetContent`, provide either:
  - an explicit `SheetDescription`, or
  - `aria-describedby={undefined}` when description is intentionally omitted.
- If title text must be visually hidden, keep it accessible with `className="sr-only"`.
- Do not merge code that introduces a `DialogContent` without a title; fix it in the same change.
- Do not import Radix dialog primitives directly in feature code; use shared wrappers from `shared/components/ui`.

## Good

```tsx
<DialogContent>
  <DialogHeader>
    <DialogTitle className="sr-only">Create suite</DialogTitle>
    <DialogDescription className="sr-only">Create a suite and configure links.</DialogDescription>
  </DialogHeader>
  ...
</DialogContent>
```

```tsx
<DialogContent aria-describedby={undefined}>
  <DialogHeader>
    <DialogTitle>Compact dialog</DialogTitle>
  </DialogHeader>
  ...
</DialogContent>
```

```tsx
<SheetContent>
  <SheetHeader>
    <SheetTitle className="sr-only">Artifact details</SheetTitle>
    <SheetDescription className="sr-only">View and edit artifact information.</SheetDescription>
  </SheetHeader>
  ...
</SheetContent>
```

## Bad

```tsx
<DialogContent>
  <div>...</div>
</DialogContent>
```
